                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.683,
                                "byte_start": 92304,
                                "byte_stop": 127099,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in Container Corporation of America against Franchise Tax Board will be announced by Mr. Justice Brennan."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.683,
                        "stop": 226.015,
                        "byte_start": 127099,
                        "byte_stop": 996454,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15140,
                            "name": "William J. Brennan, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/william_j_brennan_jr",
                            "last_name": "Brennan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2786,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -416862000,
                                    "date_end": 648450000,
                                    "appointing_president": "Dwight D. Eisenhower",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2786"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32778,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 56873,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_j_brennan.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12330,
                            "identifier": "william_j_brennan_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.683,
                                "stop": 18.965,
                                "byte_start": 127099,
                                "byte_stop": 168268,
                                "text": "This case involves a California Franchise Tax and is here on Appeal from the Court of Appeals of California."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.965,
                                "stop": 39.192,
                                "byte_start": 168268,
                                "byte_stop": 249143,
                                "text": "That Court sustained a tax levied under California\u0027s Franchise Tax Act against appellant, Container Corporation, rejecting Container\u0027s argument that the tax as applied to it violated the Due Process and Commerce Clause -- Clauses of the Federal Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.192,
                                "stop": 54.841,
                                "byte_start": 249143,
                                "byte_stop": 311733,
                                "text": "During the tax years involve, Container Corporation controlled some 20 foreign subsidiaries located in four Latin American and four European countries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.841,
                                "stop": 85.471,
                                "byte_start": 311733,
                                "byte_stop": 434195,
                                "text": "The California franchise tax returns filed by Container admitted, however, to include any income of these subsidiaries and also omitted all of its subsidiaries, payroll, property and sales in calculating the share of its net income which was apportionable to California under that Franchise Tax Acts three-factor formula."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.471,
                                "stop": 104.032,
                                "byte_start": 434195,
                                "byte_stop": 508487,
                                "text": "California took the position that Container should have treated its overseas subsidiaries as part of its unitary business rather than as a passive investment and increased Container\u0027s tax liability accordingly."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.032,
                                "stop": 118.479,
                                "byte_start": 508487,
                                "byte_stop": 566270,
                                "text": "Container then paid the additional amounts under protest and sued in California Superior Court for a refund, raising the constitutional challenges the increased tax."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.479,
                                "stop": 127.152,
                                "byte_start": 566270,
                                "byte_stop": 600960,
                                "text": "The Superior Court upheld California\u0027s assessment -- assessment and the California Court of Appeals affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.152,
                                "stop": 131.174,
                                "byte_start": 600960,
                                "byte_stop": 617052,
                                "text": "And we in turn affirm the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.174,
                                "stop": 143.829,
                                "byte_start": 617052,
                                "byte_stop": 667625,
                                "text": "The opinion we have filed doesn\u0027t readily land itself to oral announcement and I\u0027ll therefore only briefly state our holdings that lead to our conclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.829,
                                "stop": 153.765,
                                "byte_start": 667625,
                                "byte_stop": 707435,
                                "text": "First, we hold that California\u0027s application of the unitary business principle to Container and its foreign subsidiaries was proper."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.765,
                                "stop": 169.877,
                                "byte_start": 707435,
                                "byte_stop": 771906,
                                "text": "Second, we hold that California\u0027s use of the three-factor formula of payroll, property, and sales to apportion the income of the unitary business consisting of Container and its subsidiaries was fair."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.877,
                                "stop": 188.61,
                                "byte_start": 771906,
                                "byte_stop": 846825,
                                "text": "Third, we hold that California had no obligation under the Foreign Commerce Clause to employ the arm\u0027s length analysis used by the Federal Government and most foreign nations in evaluating the tax consequences of intercorporate relationships."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 188.61,
                                "stop": 197.547,
                                "byte_start": 846825,
                                "byte_stop": 882560,
                                "text": "Fourth, we hold that the double taxation occasioned by the California scheme is not constitutionally impermissible."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 197.547,
                                "stop": 219.321,
                                "byte_start": 882560,
                                "byte_stop": 969600,
                                "text": "Fifth and finally, we hold that the California tax does not violate the one voice standard under which a state tax at variance with federal policy will be struck down if it either implicates foreign policy issues which must be left to the Federal Government or violates a clear federal directive."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 219.321,
                                "stop": 226.015,
                                "byte_start": 969600,
                                "byte_stop": 996454,
                                "text": "Justice Powell joined by the Chief Justice and Justice O\u0027Connor has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
